.TH "crossOriginIsolated" "JS" "November 9, 2023" "JavaScript" "JavaScript Reference Manual"
.SH NAME
crossOriginIsolated \- crossOriginIsolated global property
.SH SYNOPSIS
\f[B]Note:\f[R] This feature is available in Web Workers.
.PP
The global \f[B]\f[CB]crossOriginIsolated\f[B]\f[R] read\-only property
returns a boolean value that indicates whether the website is in a
cross\-origin isolation state.
That state mitigates the risk of side\-channel attacks and unlocks a few
capabilities:
.IP \[bu] 2
\f[CR]SharedArrayBuffer\f[R] can be created and sent via a
\f[CR]Window.postMessage()\f[R] call.
.IP \[bu] 2
\f[CR]Performance.now()\f[R] offers better precision.
.IP \[bu] 2
\f[CR]Performance.measureUserAgentSpecificMemory()\f[R] can be accessed.
.PP
A website is in a cross\-origin isolated state, when the response header
\f[CR]Cross\-Origin\-Opener\-Policy\f[R] has the value
\f[CR]same\-origin\f[R] and the
\f[CR]Cross\-Origin\-Embedder\-Policy\f[R] header has the value
\f[CR]require\-corp\f[R] or \f[CR]credentialless\f[R].
.SH VALUE
A boolean value.
.SH EXAMPLES
.IP
.EX
\f[B]const\f[R] myWorker = \f[B]new\f[R] Worker(\[dq]worker.js\[dq]);

\f[B]if\f[R] (crossOriginIsolated) {
  \f[B]const\f[R] buffer = \f[B]new\f[R] SharedArrayBuffer(16);
  myWorker.postMessage(buffer);
} \f[B]else\f[R] {
  \f[B]const\f[R] buffer = \f[B]new\f[R] ArrayBuffer(16);
  myWorker.postMessage(buffer);
}
.EE
